&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;At EOS IT Solutions, we deliver innovative technology and operational support services to some of the world&#39;s most recognised organisations. We are committed to operational excellence, safety, and continuous improvement, creating an environment where our people can grow and succeed.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assembly Operative – Repair Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;We are looking for a dedicated &lt;strong&gt;Assembly Operative – Repair Service&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team supporting operations within a leading data centre environment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;This role focuses on the preparation, handling, tracking, assembly, replacement, and movement of hardware components and equipment used in repair and maintenance activities. You will work in a structured, safety-driven environment where accuracy, quality, teamwork, and adherence to procedures are essential.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Prepare hardware components, spare parts, and equipment required for repair activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Identify, scan, label, track, and update the status of components and equipment in relevant systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Carry out component assembly or replacement activities following approved procedures and work instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Support repair workflows involving servers, storage systems, network equipment, power systems, cooling equipment, and related hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Perform visual inspections and basic procedural checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Maintain accurate operational records in required tracking tools and client systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Support the controlled flow of components and equipment within the Repair Service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Maintain an organised and compliant workspace in line with 5S and site standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Use tools and equipment safely and correctly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Escalate damaged equipment, missing components, process deviations, or other non-standard situations to the supervisor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Collaborate with colleagues, supervisors, client representatives, and other site stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Follow all safety, quality, security, confidentiality, and site-access requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR COMPANY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EOS IT Solutions is a Global Technology and Logistics company, providing Collaboration and Business IT Support services to some of the world’s largest industry leaders, delivering forward-thinking solutions based on multi-domain architecture. Customer satisfaction and commitment to superior quality of service are our top business priorities, along with investing in and supporting our partners and employees.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are a true International IT provider and are proud to deliver our services through global simplicity with trusted transparency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a skilled and detail-oriented &lt;strong data-start=&quot;811&quot; data-end=&quot;840&quot;&gt;AV Commissioning Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the testing, configuration, and fine-tuning of complex audio-visual systems. In this role, you’ll collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure AV systems are delivered to the highest quality standards and meet client expectations. This is an excellent opportunity for a hands-on AV professional with strong technical acumen and a passion for delivering world-class AV experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with project teams to review and understand AV designs and specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform on-site testing and commissioning of AV systems, ensuring full functionality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure, program, and integrate AV components including displays, projectors, audio processors, and control systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calibrate AV systems for optimal audio and video performance (levels, resolutions, color accuracy)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues during commissioning and handover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate signal flow and connectivity across all AV components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and test AV control systems (touch panels, automation, user interfaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document configuration settings, commissioning results, and system adjustments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide training and operational support to end-users and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with designers and programmers to optimize system performance and user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL CRITERIA:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in AV commissioning or a similar technical AV role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of AV hardware and protocols (HDMI, HDBaseT, Dante, AES67)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in AV calibration techniques and the use of testing tools (e.g., signal generators, analyzers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AV control and DSP platforms such as Crestron, Extron, Biamp, or QSC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional troubleshooting and diagnostic skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented and highly organized, with a commitment to high-quality delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work both independently and in a team setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to travel to client/project sites as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DESIRABLE CRITERIA:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Electrical Engineering, Audio Engineering, Computer Science, or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Industry certifications such as CTS (Certified Technology Specialist)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in enterprise environments or large-scale AV deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in control system programming or GUI customization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with remote monitoring tools or AV over IP technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience training end-users and conducting technical walkthroughs&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;EOS IT Solutions is a Global Technology and Logistics company, providing Collaboration and Business IT Support services to some of the world’s largest industry leaders, delivering forward-thinking solutions based on multi-domain architecture. Customer satisfaction and commitment to superior quality of service are our top business priorities, along with investing in and supporting our partners and employees.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are a true International IT provider and are proud to deliver our services through global simplicity with trusted transparency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION OVERVIEW:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;We are seeking an Infrastructure Engineer to join our Audiovisual Engineering team. This technical role supports the global AV ecosystem that powers seamless communication and collaboration across the company. You’ll be responsible for the implementation, support, administration, and life cycle management of audio/video hardware and software, focusing not only on reliability, but also on automation, scripting, and operational scalability. The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience with commercial AV technologies (QSC Q-SYS, Shure, Dante), video conferencing systems (Google Meet, Zoom), and converged IP networks, paired with a strong foundation in automation tools, programming, and infrastructure as code. You’ll play a key role in driving innovation, improving support processes, and building repeatable solutions that reduce manual overhead. This position involves full lifecycle project ownership—from requirements gathering and design reviews through deployment and operational support—and may require occasional off-hours work.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;job-posting-section&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Own the implementation and support of AV technologies for deployment projects globally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with architects, engineers, and AV integrators to design, automate, and deploy solutions that align with company standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage scripts, tools, and automation pipelines for provisioning and managing AV systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze, test, install, document, and support audio/video over IP solutions in a global, converged network environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) to support AV operations and upgrades in production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce scopes of work, documentation (including AV schematics), and vendor communications for new AV installations or retrofits.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Identify and recommend new technologies or automation strategies to improve scalability and efficiency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed documentation of deployed AV configurations, including change history and versioning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or assist in root cause analysis and long-term resolution of AV issues; mentor junior engineers in troubleshooting and automation techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage project timelines, resource estimates, and product refresh schedules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as Tier 3 support for complex AV issues and escalations in production environments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel up to 20% for deployments, testing, and operational support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL NEED TO SUCCEED:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp

