&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Collaboration Services Team&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for supporting the installation, maintenance and&amp;nbsp;troubleshooting of all audio-visual equipment in our client’s managed venue spaces, broadcast&amp;nbsp;studios &amp;amp; customer experience centers. Our objective is to create a highly meaningful,&amp;nbsp;impactful &amp;amp; supportive team that enables all of our technicians to have an impactful role in all&amp;nbsp;areas of the service we provide onsite. As an entry level technician you will work alongside our&amp;nbsp;Senior Technicians &amp;amp; System Engineers to provide dedicated support to our client’s in-house&amp;nbsp;Audio-Visual Operations team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily maintenance of hardware &amp;amp; software for the internal platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kick off meetings &amp;amp; events (Experience Center &amp;amp; Event Space) with AV/IT Support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute monthly preventative maintenance on all hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize remote access tools on Mac, Linux &amp;amp; Windows systems to control the internal&amp;nbsp;platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with clients to identify needs &amp;amp; evaluate solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide onsite support for visitors and executive level events as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support event operation technicians with all issues relating to event spaces prior to&amp;nbsp;events.&lt;/li&gt;
